a:18:{s:4:"name";s:7:"Provera";s:11:"small_descr";s:142:"Provera improves  women's condition when menstrual periods have stopped or in case of an abnormal bleeding of uterus due to hormone imbalance.";s:14:"small_descr_de";s:156:"Provera verbessert Bedingung von Frauen, deren Menstruationsperioden haben wegen der Hormonangehalten oder im Falle einer anomalen Blutung der Gebärmutter.";s:14:"small_descr_fr";s:172:"Provera améliore les conditions des femmes dont les périodes menstruelles se sont interrompues ou en cas d'un saignement utérin anormal lié au déséquilibre d'hormone.";s:14:"small_descr_es";s:160:"Provera mejora la condición de mujeres cuyos períodos menstruales se han parado o en caso de una sangría anormal del útero debido al desequilibrio hormonal.";s:14:"small_descr_it";s:161:"Provera migliora la condizione delle donne i cui periodi mestruali hanno smesso o in caso di sanguinamento anomalo dell'utero a causa di uno squilibrio ormonale.";s:10:"full_descr";s:3889:"<p><strong>Common use<br /></strong><br /> Provera contains medroxyprogesterone acetate, female hormone used to regulate ovulation and menstrual periods. The medication is used to treat secondary amenorrhea and abnormal uterine bleeding caused by hormonal imbalance (fibroids, uterine cancer), to reduce the incidence of endometrial hyperplasia in postmenopausal women.<br /><br /> <strong>Dosage and direction<br /></strong><br /> Take 5 or 10 mg of this medication daily for 5 -10 days. Take in strict accordance with recommendations of your doctor. Avoid taking larger amounts of the medication. Your doctor may administer to start taking the medication on a certain day of your menses. While you are on Provera, examine your breasts for lumps on a monthly basis. Provera may change results of certain medical tests. Inform your doctor that you are taking this drug.<br /><br /> <strong>Precautions<br /></strong><br /> Do not smoke while taking Provera, unless risk of blood clotting increases. Inform your doctor about conditions you may have as dose adjustment may be required: hypertension, heart disease, recent stroke or heart attack, congestive heart failure, hypercalcinemia, high cholesterol or triglycerides, recent miscarriage or abortion, severe pelvic pain, asthma, migraine headaches, epilepsy, a thyroid disorder, diabetes, kidney disease, lupus, depression.<br /><br /> <strong>Contraindications</strong><br /><br /> Do not take this medication if you have hypersensitivity to its components, pregnant, suffer with a hormone-related cancer of genitals or mammary gland, abnormal vaginal bleeding that has not been diagnosed, have liver disease, a history of stroke or blood clot, or breastfeed.<br /><br /> <strong>Side effects<br /></strong><br /> The most frequent side effects of Provera are headache, dizziness, irritability, insomnia, drowsiness, fatigue, depression, nausea, abdominal pain, thrombophlebitis, cerebrovascular disorders, hypersensitivity nipple breast, galactorrhoea, erosion of the cervix, dysmenorrhea. High doses of the medication may produce acne, hirsutism, changes in body weight, moon face, hyperthermia, alopecia. Allergic reactions such as hives, rash, facial swelling and difficulty breathing are also possible.<br /><br /> <strong>Drug interaction</strong><br /><br /> Aminoglutethimide reduces plasma concentrations and reduces efficiency of Provera. Inform your doctor about all prescribed and over-the-counter medications, herbal products, vitamins and food supplements you use.<br /><br /> <strong>Missed dose<br /></strong><br /> Never take a double dose of this medication. If it is almost time of the next dose, just skip the missed portion and continue taking the medicine according to the schedule.<br /><br /> <strong>Overdose<br /></strong><br /> Overdose symptoms may be: dizziness, drowsiness, stomach pain, nausea, vomiting, breast tenderness, or vaginal bleeding. Seek immediate medical help if you experience the symptoms listed above.<br /><br /> <strong>Storage<br /></strong><br /> Store at room temperature between 20-25 C (68-77 F). Store away from moisture, heat, and sunlight. It is not recommended to store in a bathroom and places available for children. <br /><br /> <strong>Disclaimer <br /></strong><br /> We provide only general information about medications which does not cover all directions, possible drug integrations, or precautions. Information at the site cannot be used for self-treatment and self-diagnosis. Any specific instructions for a particular patient should be agreed with your health care adviser or doctor in charge of the case. We disclaim reliability of this information and mistakes it could contain. We are not responsible for any direct, indirect, special or other indirect damage as a result of any use of the information on this site and also for consequences of self-treatment.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_de";s:3879:"<p><strong>Common use<br /></strong><br /> Provera contains medroxyprogesterone acetate, female hormone used to regulate ovulation and menstrual periods. The medication is used to treat secondary amenorrhea and abnormal uterine bleeding caused by hormonal imbalance (fibroids, uterine cancer), to reduce the incidence of endometrial hyperplasia in postmenopausal women.<br /><br /> <strong>Dosage and direction<br /></strong><br /> Take 5 or 10 mg of this medication daily for 5 to 10 days. Take exactly according to recommendations of your doctor. Avoid taking larger amounts of the medication. Your doctor may administer to start taking the medication on a certain day of your menses. While you are on Provera examine your breasts for lumps on a monthly basis. Provera may change results of certain medical tests. Inform your doctor that you take this drug.<br /><br /> <strong>Precautions<br /></strong><br /> Do not smoke while you take Provera, unless risk of blood clotting increases. Inform your doctor about conditions you may have as dose adjustment may be needed: hypertension, heart disease, recent stroke or heart attack, congestive heart failure, hypercalcinemia, high cholesterol or triglycerides, recent miscarriage or abortion, severe pelvic pain, asthma, migraine headaches, epilepsy, a thyroid disorder, diabetes, kidney disease, lupus, depression.<br /><br /> <strong>Contraindications<br /></strong><br /> Do not take this medication if you have hypersensitivity to its components, pregnant, suffer with a hormone-related cancer of genitals or mammary gland, abnormal vaginal bleeding that has not been diagnosed, have liver disease, a history of stroke or blood clot, or breastfeed.<br /><br /> <strong>Side effects<br /></strong><br /> The most frequent side effects of Provera are headache, dizziness, irritability, insomnia, drowsiness, fatigue, depression, nausea, abdominal pain, thrombophlebitis, cerebrovascular disorders, hypersensitivity nipple breast, galactorrhoea, erosion of the cervix, dysmenorrhea. High doses of the medication may produce acne, hirsutism, changes in body weight, moon face, hyperthermia, alopecia. Allergic reactions such as hives, rash, facial swelling and difficulty breathing are also possible.<br /><br /> <strong>Drug interaction</strong><br /><br /> Aminoglutethimide reduces plasma concentrations and reduces efficiency of Provera. Inform your doctor about all prescribed and over-the-counter medications, herbal products, vitamins and food supplements you use.<br /><br /> <strong>Missed dose<br /></strong><br /> Never take a double dose of this medication. If it is almost time of the next dose just skip the missed portion and continue to take the medicine according to the schedule.<br /><br /> <strong>Overdose<br /></strong><br /> Overdose symptoms may be: dizziness, drowsiness, stomach pain, nausea, vomiting, breast tenderness, or vaginal bleeding. Seek immediate medical help if you experience the symptoms listed above.<br /><br /> <strong>Storage<br /></strong><br /> Store at room temperature between 20-25 C (68-77 F). Store away from moisture, heat, and sunlight. It is not recommended to store in a bathroom and places available for children. <br /><br /> <strong>Disclaimer <br /></strong><br /> We provide only general information about medications which does not cover all directions, possible drug integrations, or precautions. Information at the site cannot be used for self-treatment and self-diagnosis. Any specific instructions for a particular patient should be agreed with your health care adviser or doctor in charge of the case. We disclaim reliability of this information and mistakes it could contain. We are not responsible for any direct, indirect, special or other indirect damage as a result of any use of the information on this site and also for consequences of self-treatment.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_fr";s:6075:"<p><strong>Usage g&eacute;n&eacute;ral<br /></strong><br /> Provera contient de l'ac&eacute;tate de m&eacute;droxyprogest&eacute;rone, hormone f&eacute;minin utilis&eacute; dans le traitement de la r&eacute;gulation de l'ovulation et des p&eacute;riodes menstruelles. Le m&eacute;dicament est utilis&eacute; pour traiter l&rsquo;am&eacute;norrh&eacute;e secondaire et le saignement ut&eacute;rin anormal provoqu&eacute; par le d&eacute;s&eacute;quilibre hormonal (fibromes, cancer ut&eacute;rin), pour r&eacute;duire l'incidence l&rsquo;hyperplasie endom&eacute;triale chez les femmes d&rsquo;&acirc;ge postm&eacute;nopausique.<br /><br /> <strong>Dosage et administration</strong><br /><br /> Prenez 5 ou 10 mg de ce m&eacute;dicament tous les jours pendant 5 &agrave; 10 jours. Prenez le m&eacute;dicament suivant exactement les recommandations de votre m&eacute;decin. Evitez de prendre de plus grandes quantit&eacute;s du m&eacute;dicament. Votre m&eacute;decin peut vous recommander un d&eacute;but de prise du m&eacute;dicament &agrave; un jour d&eacute;fini de votre menstruation. Au cours de la p&eacute;riode de traitement par Provera, faites examiner mensuellement vos seins pour d&eacute;celer les tum&eacute;factions &eacute;ventuelles. Provera peut influencer sur les r&eacute;sultats de certains tests m&eacute;dicaux. Informez votre m&eacute;decin sur la prise de ce m&eacute;dicament.<br /><br /> <strong>Pr&eacute;cautions<br /></strong><br /> Ne fumez pendant la p&eacute;riode o&ugrave; vous prenez Provera, &agrave; moins que ne s&rsquo;acc&eacute;l&egrave;re le risque de coagulation du sang. Informez votre m&eacute;decin de vos conditions, du fait qu&rsquo;une rectification de dose pourrait &ecirc;tre n&eacute;cessaire : l'hypertension, une maladie du c&oelig;ur, une attaque r&eacute;cente ou une crise cardiaque, un arr&ecirc;t congestif du coeur, l&rsquo;hypercalcin&eacute;mie, un haut niveau de cholest&eacute;rol ou des triglyc&eacute;rides, une fausse couche r&eacute;cente ou un avortement, une douleur pelvienne aigue, l'asthme, des maux de t&ecirc;te sous forme de migraine, l'&eacute;pilepsie, des insuffisances de la thyro&iuml;de, le diab&egrave;te, une maladie du rein, un lupus, une d&eacute;pression.<br /><br /> <strong>Contre-indications</strong><br /><br /> Ne prenez pas ce m&eacute;dicament si vous avez l'hypersensibilit&eacute; &agrave; ses composantes, enceinte, ou souffrez d&rsquo;un cancer d&ucirc; &agrave; une hormone d'organes g&eacute;nitaux ou des glandes mammaires, un saignement vaginal anormal qui n'a pas &eacute;t&eacute; diagnostiqu&eacute;, une maladie de foie, une histoire de d&rsquo;acc&egrave;s ou de caillot sanguin, ou si vous allaitez.<br /><br /><strong>Effets secondaires possibles<br /></strong><br /> Les effets secondaires les plus fr&eacute;quents de Provera sont les maux de t&ecirc;te, le vertige, l'irritabilit&eacute;, l'insomnie, la somnolence, la fatigue, la d&eacute;pression, la naus&eacute;e, les douleurs abdominales, la thrombophl&eacute;bite, les insuffisances c&eacute;r&eacute;brovasculaires, l'hypersensibilit&eacute; du mamelon du sein, lq galactorrh&eacute;e, l'&eacute;rosion du col de l'ut&eacute;rus, la dysm&eacute;norrh&eacute;e. De hautes doses du m&eacute;dicament peuvent provoquer l'acn&eacute;, l&rsquo;hirsutisme, les changements du poids du corps, le givrage du visage, l&rsquo;hyperthermie, l'alop&eacute;cie. Les r&eacute;actions allergiques telles que les &eacute;ruptions, les rougeurs, l'enflure du visage et les troubles de respiration sont &eacute;galement possibles.<br /><br /> <strong>Interaction des m&eacute;dicaments</strong><br /><br /> L&rsquo;aminoglut&eacute;thimide r&eacute;duit la concentration du plasma et r&eacute;duit l'efficacit&eacute; de Provera. Informez votre docteur de tous les m&eacute;dicaments prescrits sur ordonnance et sans ordonnance, des produits &agrave; base d&rsquo;herbes, des vitamines et des additifs alimentaires que vous prenez.<br /><br /> <strong>Omission de dose<br /></strong><br /> Ne prenez jamais une double dose de ce m&eacute;dicament. Si l&rsquo;heure de la dose suivante est proche sautez simplement la dose omise et continuez &agrave; prendre le m&eacute;dicament selon le programme fix&eacute;.<br /><br /> <strong>Surdosage<br /></strong><br /> Les sympt&ocirc;mes de surdosage peuvent &ecirc;tre : le vertige, la somnolence, la douleur a l'estomac, la naus&eacute;e, le vomissement, l&rsquo;hypersensibilit&eacute; des seins, ou le saignement vaginal. Contactez l'assistance m&eacute;dicale urgente si vous constatez les sympt&ocirc;mes &eacute;num&eacute;r&eacute;s ci-dessus.<br /><br /><strong>Conservation<br /></strong><br /> Conservez &agrave; la temp&eacute;rature de chambre entre 20-25 C (68-77 F). Gardez le m&eacute;dicament &agrave; l&rsquo;abri de l'humidit&eacute;, de la chaleur et de la lumi&egrave;re du soleil. Il n&rsquo;est pas recommande pas de le conserver dans la salle de bains et &agrave; des endroits accessibles aux enfants.<br /><br /> <strong>Disclaimer (avis de non responsabilit&eacute;)</strong><br /><br /> Nous fournissons des renseignements &agrave; caract&egrave;res uniquement g&eacute;n&eacute;raux sur les m&eacute;dicaments qui n&rsquo;englobent pas tous les domaines, les polyvalences possibles du m&eacute;dicament, ou les pr&eacute;cautions. Les renseignements sur le site ne peuvent &ecirc;tre utilis&eacute;s pour un traitement personnel et un diagnostic personnel. Toute instruction sp&eacute;cifique pour un patient particulier devrait &ecirc;tre consult&eacute;e avec votre conseiller de soins de sant&eacute; ou votre m&eacute;decin responsable du cas. Nous refusons toute r&eacute;f&eacute;rence au caract&egrave;re ind&eacute;niable de ces renseignements et des erreurs qu'ils pourraient contenir. Nous ne sommes pas responsables de tout dommage direct ou indirect, sp&eacute;cial ou d&rsquo;autre dommage &agrave; la suite de toute utilisation des renseignements sur ce site et &eacute;galement pour les cons&eacute;quences de l&rsquo;auto-traitement.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_es";s:4714:"<p><strong>Propiedades<br /></strong><br /> Provera es acid medroxiprogestrona, hormona femenina usada para regular ovulaci&oacute;n y periodos mensrtuales. La medicina se usa para curar amenorrea secundaria y hemorragia abnormal de &uacute;tero causada por inbalance hormonal (miomas, c&aacute;ncer de &uacute;tero), para disminuir morbilidad de hiperplasia endomentral a las mujeras con postmenopausa.<br /><br /><strong>Posolog&iacute;a y forma de administraci&oacute;n<br /></strong><br /> Tome 5 o 10 mg de esta medicina al d&iacute;a durante 5-10 d&iacute;as.Tomela seg&uacute;n las recomendaciones de su doctor.Evite tomar cantidades grandes de ella. Su m&eacute;dico puede ajustar empezar tomarla en cierto d&iacute;a de su menstruaci&oacute;n. Durante toma de Provera examine suspecho en hichaz&oacute;nes cada mes. Provera puede cambiar algunos resultados de su testos medicas.informe a su doctor sobre toma de esta medicina.<br /><br /> <strong>Precauciones</strong><br /><br /> No se puede fumar durante toma de Provera pues este puede aumentar riesgo de tromb&oacute;geno. Informe a su doctor sobre condiciones que usted puede tener porque puede ser necesitada prescripci&oacute;n de dosis: hipertensi&oacute;n, enfermedad card&iacute;aca, paroximo reciente o ataque card&iacute;aca, insuficiencia card&iacute;aca congente, hipercalcemia, colesterol o triglic&eacute;ridos alto, aborto reciente, dolor pelvica grave, atma, migra&ntilde;a, dolor de cabeza, diabitis, enfermedad de ri&ntilde;ones, depresi&oacute;n, lupus, desorden tiroide.<br /><br /> <strong>Contradicones<br /></strong><br /> No se puede tomar esta medicina si Usted tiene sensibilidad excesiva a sus componentes, si Usted est&aacute; emborazada, tiene c&aacute;ncer relacionado a hormona de genitalia o de glandula mamaria, hemorragia vaginal abnormal no revalada, tiene enfermedad de h&iacute;gado, historia de paroximo o tromb&oacute;geno, lactaci&oacute;n.<br /><br /> <strong>Reacciones adversas posibles<br /></strong><br /> Los efectos secundarios m&aacute;s frecuentes son dolor de cabeza, v&eacute;rtigo, irritabilidad, insomnio, somnolencia, cansancio, depresi&oacute;n, dolor abdomonal, n&aacute;usea, tromboflebitis, desorden cerebrovascular, sensibilidad excesiva de mamel&oacute;n, glalactorroea, erosi&oacute;n de cuella de la matriz, disminorrea. Dosis altas de esta medicina puede producir acn&eacute;, abundancia de pelo, cambios de peso de cuerpo, cara de Luna, apolecia. Tamb&iacute;&eacute;n reacciones alergicas son posibles tales como erupci&oacute;n, exantema, hichaz&oacute;n de cara y dificiultad de respiraci&oacute;n.<br /><br /> <strong>Interacci&oacute;n con otros medicamentos</strong><br /><br /> Aminoglutetimida desminuye concentraci&oacute;n de plasma y as&iacute; disminuye efectividad de Provera. Informe a su doctor sobre todas medicinas prescritas y no, productos de hierba y sumplementos de comida y vitaminas que Usted usa.<br /><br /> <strong>Dosis omitida<br /></strong><br /> Nunca se puede tomar dosis doble de esta medicina.Si es casi la hora para la dosis siguiente, omita la dosis omitida y vuelva a su horario regular.<br /><br /> <strong>Sobredosis<br /></strong><br /> Los s&iacute;ntomas de sobredosis pueden ser somnolencia, v&eacute;rtigo, dolor da et&oacute;mago, sensibilidad de pecho, y hemorragia vaginal.Busque ayuda medica urgente si Usted siente s&iacute;ntomas dados.<br /><br /> <strong>Almacenamiento<br /></strong><br /> Se debe almacenar Provera a una temperatura de 20-25 C (68-77 F), del alcance de humedad,los rayos solares y calor. No se recomienda almacenar en cuarto de ba&ntilde;o o en lugare accesible a los ni&ntilde;os.<br /><br /> <strong>Descargo de responsabilidades<br /></strong><br /> Proveemos una informaci&oacute;n del car&aacute;cter general sobre los medicamentos sin intentar cubrir todas las recomendaciones, totalidad de los casos de interacci&oacute;n con otros medicamentos, tampoco todas las precauciones existentes. La informaci&oacute;n de la presente p&aacute;gina web no puede ser de utilidad en el autotratamiento ni el autodiagn&oacute;stico. Todas las recomendaciones espec&iacute;ficas para cada paciente individual deben arreglarse con el coordinador designado de la salud p&uacute;blica o con el m&eacute;dico encargado del caso cl&iacute;nico. Renunciamos de todas las responsabilidades por la fiabilidad del material provisto ni por errores que contenga. Nos descargamos de responsabilidad por los da&ntilde;os, sean que sean directos, indirectos, espec&iacute;ficos o dem&aacute;s da&ntilde;os que resulten de la aplicaci&oacute;n del contenido de la presente p&aacute;gina web ni que sean consecuencias del autotratamiento</p>";s:13:"full_descr_it";s:4431:"<p><strong>Uso comune</strong><br /><br /> Provera contiene medrossiprogesterone acetato, ormoni femminili usati per regolare l'ovulazione e periodi mestruali. Il farmaco &egrave; usato per curare l'amenorrea secondaria e sanguinamento uterino anomalo causata da uno squilibrio ormonale (fibromi, tumore uterino), per ridurre l'incidenza di iperplasia endometriale in donne in postmenopausa.<br /><br /> <strong>Dosaggio e direzione<br /></strong><br /> Prendete 5 o 10 mg di questo farmaco al giorno per 5 a 10 giorni. Prendere esattamente secondo le raccomandazioni del suo medico. Evitare l'assunzione di elevate quantit&agrave; di farmaci. Il medico pu&ograve; somministrare per iniziare a prendere il farmaco in un determinato giorno del tuo ciclo mestruale. Mentre si &egrave; in Provera per esaminare il seno grumi su base mensile. Provera pu&ograve; modificare i risultati di alcuni esami medici. Informare il vostro medico che si prende questo farmaco.<br /><br /> <strong>Precauzioni</strong><br /><br /> Non fumare mentre si prende Provera, a meno che non aumenta il rischio di coagulazione del sangue. Informare il vostro medico circa le condizioni si possono avere come aggiustamento della dose pu&ograve; essere necessaria: ipertensione, malattie cardiache, ictus recente o attacco cardiaco, insufficienza cardiaca congestizia, hypercalcinemia, colesterolo o trigliceridi, recente dolore aborto spontaneo o un aborto, gravi pelviche, asma, emicrania , l'epilessia, una malattia della tiroide, diabete, malattie renali, il lupus, la depressione.<br /><br /> <strong>Controindicazioni<br /></strong><br /> Non assumere questo farmaco se si dispone di ipersensibilit&agrave; ai suoi componenti, in gravidanza, soffre di un tumore ormono-correlati dei genitali o di ghiandola mammaria, anormale sanguinamento vaginale che non &egrave; stata diagnosticata, ha una malattia al fegato, una storia di ictus o di coagulo di sangue, o allattare al seno.<br /><br /> <strong>Effetti collaterali<br /></strong><br /> Gli effetti collaterali pi&ugrave; frequenti di Provera sono mal di testa, vertigini, irritabilit&agrave;, insonnia, sonnolenza, stanchezza, depressione, nausea, dolore addominale, tromboflebiti, disordini cerebrovascolari, capezzolo del seno di ipersensibilit&agrave;, galattorrea, l'erosione della cervice, dismenorrea. Alte dosi di farmaco pu&ograve; produrre acne, irsutismo, variazioni del peso corporeo, il volto della luna, ipertermia, alopecia. Reazioni allergiche come orticaria, rash, gonfiore facciale e difficolt&agrave; di respirazione sono inoltre possibili.<br /><br /> <strong>Interazione farmacologica<br /></strong><br /> Aminoglutetimide riduce le concentrazioni plasmatiche e riduce l'efficienza di Provera. Informare il vostro medico su tutti i farmaci prescritti e over-the-counter, prodotti a base di erbe, vitamine e integratori alimentari che si usa.<br /><br /> <strong>Dose<br /></strong><br /> Non prendere mai una doppia dose di questo farmaco. Se &egrave; quasi ora della dose successiva saltare la parte dimenticata e continuare ad assumere il farmaco secondo il calendario.<br /><br /> <strong>Overdose<br /></strong><br /> sintomi di sovradosaggio possono essere: capogiri, sonnolenza, mal di stomaco, nausea, vomito, tensione mammaria, o sanguinamento vaginale. Richiedere immediatamente assistenza medica se si verificano i sintomi sopra elencati.<br /><br /> <strong>Conservazione<br /></strong><br /> Conservare a temperatura ambiente tra i 20-25 C (68-77 F). Conservare lontano da umidit&agrave;, calore e luce solare. Non si raccomanda di conservare in un bagno e posti disponibili per i bambini.<br /><br /> <strong>Declinazione della responsabilita</strong><br /><br /> Noi forniamo solo informazioni di carattere generale su farmaci che non copre tutte le direzioni, integrazioni farmacologiche, o precauzioni. Informazioni presso il sito non pu&ograve; essere utilizzato per l'auto-trattamento e di auto-diagnosi. Eventuali istruzioni specifiche per un particolare paziente deve essere concordato con il proprio consulente sanitario o medico incaricato del caso. Decliniamo l'affidabilit&agrave; di queste informazioni e potrebbe contenere errori. Noi non siamo responsabili per qualsiasi danno diretto, indiretto, speciale o altre indiretta, a seguito di qualsiasi ut